    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, the doctor says i have to keep k levels stable, but if i'm eating enough spinach to basically flood my system with it, wouldn't i be in control of it myself? it feels like i'm just managing my own levels with food instead of a pill. if i'm really consistent with the smoothies and the garlic every single morning, can't i just taper myself off slowly instead of having to do the blood tests? it seems way more logical to just use what my body already knows how to process.",
